LABOUR
Minister Mildred Oliphant announced on Monday night, that the introduction of the
National Minimum Wage by May will not be possible.According to Oliphant,
the delay is because Parliament won’t be able to finalise the Bills aimed at
implementing the new policy by that date.Oliphant  mentioned that the Bills were only referred to
