Parliament to process the Bills," Oliphant said.The Labour
Relations Amendment Bill and the Basic Conditions of Employment Bill contains
amendments that are important to the National Minimum Wage Bill.The Bill
proposes that the National Minimum Wage be set at R20 per hour and be reviewed
annually.The minimum
wages for domestic and farm workers will initially be set at R15 and R18 an
hour respectively.This will be
adjusted to be brought on par with the National Minimum Wage within two years
of its implementation.